Subject: Re: [T2] how do you test the oxygen sensor

At 04:00 PM 11/11/2003, Andrew Mueller wrote:
>How do you test if the oxygen sensor in the exhaust is
>still working?  I have an 83CA emissions vanagon.

Since nobody has answered yet, I'll have a go.

If you have an analog voltmeter you should be able to tap into the wiring and verify that the signal is oscillating between roughly .3v and .7v.  Assuming of course that your engine is idling, and tuned properly.

-David
